# Karpathy Guardrails

Apply these four principles to every code change in this project.
Full agent spec: `~/Agents/agents/karpathy-guardrails.md`

## 1. Think Before Coding
State the goal in one sentence before touching any file.
Identify the entry point, call chain, and files that will change.

## 2. Simplicity First
Prefer fewer files, fewer abstractions, shortest path to passing tests.
No new dependencies unless confirmed necessary.

## 3. Surgical Changes
Change only what is required for the goal.
Do not reformat, rename, or touch code outside the affected region.

## 4. Goal-Driven Execution
Every edit traces back to the stated goal.
Stop when the acceptance criterion is met. Do not gold-plate.
